"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48740","Cabinet Office","false","2014-05-01","<p>The deduction of trade union subscriptions from payroll through check-off is a matter delegated to Departments.</p><p>Departments should keep these arrangements under review to ensure that they are appropriate and meet the needs of a modern workplace, as per section 7.3.3 of the Civil Service management code.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48740/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48740/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48740/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, for what reasons his Department requested that government departments review the check-off system for union subscriptions.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","196913"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48741","Cabinet Office","false","2014-05-01","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48741/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48741/answer","PQ 196862.pdf","Working Age Population - ONS Letter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48741/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the change in the percentage of working age population employed by the public sector was in (a) England, (b) Wales, (c) Scotland and (d) Northern Ireland between 2012 and 2013.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","196862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48742","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-01","<p>The Government is aware of the impact that costs can have on investment returns. While there are currently no plans for HM Treasury to undertake a review the Government is working with the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), which regulates the disclosure of fees and expenses in accordance with existing regulation.</p><p> </p><p>The FCA has conducted a review on the clarity of fund charges within the current regulatory framework to ensure costs are clearly set out to consumers. It will publish its findings in quarter 2 2014. The FCA has also worked closely with the Treasury to shape future European legislation which will improve the disclosure of fund charges across Europe.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48742/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48742/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48742/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will review the level and practice of undeclared costings charged by financial institutions to private investors on open-ended investment trusts and other products.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","196864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48743","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-01","<p>In accordance with the Loans to Ireland Act 2010, HM Treasury reports to Parliament every six months including information on the outstanding principal. I refer the hon. Gentleman to the report laid on 28 April 2014 which is also available online, alongside all previous reports submitted by HM Treasury, on the following site:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/bilateral-loan-to-ireland" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/bilateral-loan-to-ireland</a>.</p><p> </p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48743/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48743/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48743/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much the government of the Irish Republic currently owes the UK; and when he expects the amount outstanding to be repaid in full.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","196865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48744","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-01","<p><strong>Figures for 2013-14 are not yet available.</strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>The latest available estimates (from 2011-12) of the number of people receiving income tax deductions for their personal pension contributions and the value of deductions by different income levels can be found in Table 3.8 at the following link:</strong></p><p> </p><p><strong><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/276037/tables3-1_3-11.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/276037/tables3-1_3-11.pdf</a></strong></p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48744/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48744/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48744/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much in income tax relief was added to the personal pensions of higher rate taxpayers in 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","196866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48745","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Crown Estate operates commercially at arm's length from the Treasury. The Crown Estate makes commercial decisions in line with the Crown Estate Act 1961 and does not normally discuss them in detail with the Treasury.</p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan","196908 ; 196909","2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48745/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48745/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48745/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many Crown Estate houses the Crown Estate plans to sell.","false","Biography information for Mr Jeremy Browne","Taunton Deane","Mr Jeremy Browne","196886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48746","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p>The information is not available. HMRC's administrative systems do not separately identify mortgage interest payments against residential property from other financial costs incurred across all types of property businesses (both residential and non-residential). Moreover property income is grouped with other income in the calculation of tax liabilities, and consequently the amounts of specific deductions effective against each rate of tax is not precisely defined.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48746/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48746/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48746/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much tax relief was provided for mortgage interest payments by buy-to-let residential property investors at the (a) basic income tax marginal rate, (b) higher income tax marginal rate and (c) additional income tax marginal rate in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12 and (iii) 2012-13.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","196905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48747","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p>The information is not available. HMRC's administrative systems do not distinguish between residential and non-residential property businesses nor the nature of rental property businesses such as buy-to-let investors. Moreover property income is grouped with other income in the calculation of tax liabilities, and consequently the amounts of specific deductions effective against each rate of tax is not precisely defined.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48747/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48747/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48747/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much of each type of tax relief was provided to buy-to-let residential property investors at the (a) basic income tax marginal rate, (b) higher income tax marginal rate and (c) additional income tax marginal rate in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12 and (iii) 2012-13.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","196906"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48748","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p>The information is not available. HMRC's administrative systems do not distinguish between residential and non-residential property businesses nor the nature of rental property businesses such as buy-to-let investors. Moreover property income is grouped with other income in the calculation of tax liabilities, and consequently the amounts of specific deductions effective against each rate of tax is not precisely defined.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48748/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48748/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48748/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much tax relief was provided to buy-to-let residential property investors at the (a) basic income tax marginal rate, (b) higher income tax marginal rate and (c) additional income tax marginal rate in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12 and (iii) 2012-13.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","196907"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48749","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-01","<p><strong>Treasury Ministers and officials meet with, and receive representations from, a wide range of organisations and individuals in the public and private sector as part of the usual policymaking process. It is not Government practice to provide details of all such representations.</strong></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48749/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48749/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48749/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent discussions he has had with banks about the closure of branches; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","196915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48750","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Crown Estate operates commercially at arm's length from the Treasury. The Crown Estate makes commercial decisions in line with the Crown Estate Act 1961 and does not normally discuss them in detail with the Treasury.</p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan","196886 ; 196909","2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48750/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48750/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48750/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions his Department has had with the Crown Estate on selling houses.","false","Biography information for Mr Jeremy Browne","Taunton Deane","Mr Jeremy Browne","196908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48751","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-07","<p>The Crown Estate operates commercially at arm's length from the Treasury. The Crown Estate makes commercial decisions in line with the Crown Estate Act 1961 and does not normally discuss them in detail with the Treasury.</p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan","196886 ; 196908","2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48751/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48751/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48751/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many houses the Crown Estate is proposing to sell in Taunton Deane.","false","Biography information for Mr Jeremy Browne","Taunton Deane","Mr Jeremy Browne","196909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48752","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p>The Government takes the enforcement of the National Minimum Wage (NMW) very seriously. HMRC review every complaint that is referred to them by the Pay and Work Rights Helpline. In addition, by collating and analysing data received from various sources, HMRC ensure targeted enforcement through robust risk assessment processes to identify employers across the United Kingdom who are more likely to be not paying NMW.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC deploys resources to risk, so work relating to a specific geographical area is not always undertaken by the NMW team based in that area. In addition, the NMW Dynamic Response Team (DRT) provides a multi-agency response to emerging risks, high profile casework and compliance initiatives across the UK.</p><p> </p><p>Staff across HMRC contribute to enforcing the NMW, including people who work in legal advice, debt management, technical support and criminal investigation, but HMRC does not record the specific numbers of those staff involved, beyond those identified above.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48752/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48752/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48752/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in HM Revenue and Customs' National Minimum Wage team were monitoring Scotland in each year from 2010 to 2014.","false","Biography information for Pamela Nash","Airdrie and Shotts","Pamela Nash","196927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48753","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p><strong>The Government published its top 40 priority infrastructure investments in its National Infrastructure Plan (December 2013). This included projected construction start and finish dates. The relevant information is contained in Annex A of the Plan, accessible here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-infrastructure-plan-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-infrastructure-plan-2013</a></strong></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48753/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48753/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48753/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the next 40 infrastructure projects are that the Government plans to undertake; and in what order the Government plans to undertake those projects.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48754","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p>The Government believes that there is a powerful case for giving local business and political leaders the levers they need to create jobs and drive growth. In ‘Investing in Britain's Future', the Government accepted Lord Heseltine's recommendations to devolve economic power to Local Enterprise Partnerships (LEPs) through the creation of the Local Growth Fund (LGF) with over £2 billion of budgets from skills, housing and transport for 2015-16. An area's allocation from the LGF will be available to be spent on the priorities LEPs and their partners have determined in their strategic economic plans.</p><p> </p><p>The Government allocated capital funds between programmes at Spending Review 2010 and Spending Round 2013 on the basis of a zero-based review of the economic returns of every central government capital programme, with investment being targeted increasingly at economic infrastructure. Once allocated between programmes, funds were moved into the appropriate departmental budgets to allow departments to deliver those programmes.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48754/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48754/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48754/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make it his policy to consolidate departmental funding streams into a single national infrastructure fund; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48755","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p>Treasury Ministers meet the Crown Estate Board and staff several times a year.</p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48755/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48755/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48755/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, on what occasions he has met representatives of the Crown Estate since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Mr Jeremy Browne","Taunton Deane","Mr Jeremy Browne","196955"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48756","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p><strong>This data is not available as backlog maintenance is for individual departments to manage and consequently the Treasury does not ask for the information. The Whole of Government Accounts (WGA) does include current valuations for assets across government, which takes into account the condition of the assets.</strong></p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48756/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48756/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48756/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will make an estimate of the value of backlog maintenance of central Government-owned assets.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48757","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p>Three guarantees and one Stand-by Facility have been signed under the UK Guarantees Scheme with a total value of £1,090,800,000.</p><p> </p><p>Any guarantees signed are reported to Parliament as required by the legislation, Infrastructure (Financial Assistance) Act 2012, underpinning the Scheme and can also be found on the gov.uk website.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48757/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48757/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48757/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the total value is of guarantees made under the UK Guarantees Scheme to date.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48758","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p>The UK Guarantees scheme did not exist in 2010-11. Following its introduction in 2012, Drax Power, the Northern Line Extension and Mersey Gateway Bridge are the projects in the National Infrastructure Plan that have benefited from the scheme. The total value of those three guarantees is £1,082,000,000</p><p> </p><p>The infrastructure pipeline published alongside the National Infrastructure Plan 2013 provides a forward looking, bottom-up assessment of overall planned and potential infrastructure investment in the UK to 2020 and beyond, and includes details of the projected value of individual investments. It includes large public and private infrastructure projects and capital programmes (generally worth £50 million or over) and can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-infrastructure-plan-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-infrastructure-plan-2013</a></p><p> </p><p>The pipeline has been published annually since it was first published in 2011.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48758/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48758/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48758/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the value of guarantee was of his Department's largest 200 infrastructure projects in (a) 2010-11 and (b) 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196966"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48759","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p><strong>The UK has not operated an exchange rate targeting monetary policy regime since 1992. Rather, foreign exchange reserves are currently held on a precautionary basis, to be used in the event of unexpected shocks. </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>Latest data shows that the value of the reserves is $110.9bn, up from $71.2bn in June 2010. UK imports averaged £44.4bn per month over 2013.</strong></p><p> </p>","Loughborough","Nicky Morgan",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48759/answer","Biography information for Nicky Morgan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48759/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48759/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many months of imports the UK's reserves can cover; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196967"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48760","HM Treasury","false","2014-05-06","<p><strong>The 2011 Government Construction Strategy set a target that all publicly procured construction will require fully collaborative 3D Building Information Modelling (BIM) (with all project and asset information, documentation and data being electronic) as a minimum by 2016.</strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>Infrastructure UK is working closely with the government and industry groups implementing BIM on new projects. Early adopter projects include the Ministry of Justice Cookham Wood Young Offenders Institute which has demonstrated an overall saving of around 20% with BIM as part of suite of efficiency measures deployed on the design and construction of the project. (A case study from Cookham Wood is attached to this response). </strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>Major projects and clients are now implementing BIM on new infrastructure projects. It is still too early to draw conclusive evidence of whole life benefits. However High Speed 2 has made a specific commitment to deploy BIM and the Highways Agency are piloting BIM on the new A556 trunk road project from which evidence of benefits will be collated.</strong></p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48760/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48760/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48760/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of building information modelling in reducing the total cost of ownership for complex infrastructure assets; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196968"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48761","Department for Education","false","2014-05-01","<p>The Government Actuary's Department has provided no such estimate to the Secretary of State for Education.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48761/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48761/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48761/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether the Government Actuary's Department provided Ministers with estimates of additional monies received from extra contributions to the Teachers' Pension Scheme before 19 March; and if so, if he will publish such estimates.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","196812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48762","Department for Education","false","2014-05-01","<p>The Government Actuary provides advice to the Secretary of State for Education on the valuation of the Teachers' Pension Scheme and his Department is currently finalising its work. The Secretary of State plans to publish the outcome of the valuation, including the Actuary's full report, in June 2014.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48762/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48762/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48762/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when the Government Actuary's Department will publish details of the valuation of the Teachers' Pension Scheme.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","196813"
