"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48785","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-07","<p>The costs of the Baha Mousa and Al-Sweady inquiries were not deemed by the Department to be true net additional costs associated with activity to support specifically authorised operations and were not reclaimed from the Treasury Special Reserve.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48785/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48785/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48785/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the costs of the (a) Baha Moussa inquiry and (b) Al-Sweady inquiry are classified by his Department as being operational and reclaimable from the Treasury Special Reserve.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196971"
