"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48787","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-13","<p>I regret that I must withhold the requested information as its disclosure would or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p><p> </p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2014-05-13T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48787/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48787/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48787/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library copies of his Department's output maps.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48788","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-14","<p>I am withholding the information requested as its disclosure would be commercially sensitive and would prejudice the economic interests of the United Kingdom as well as the capability, effectiveness and security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond",,"2014-05-14T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48788/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48788/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48788/answer","Runnymede and Weybridge","Mr Philip Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48788/answer/previousversion/9121","Biography information for Mr Philip Hammond","11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will place in the Library copies of his Department's force structure cost model.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196963"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48789","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-05-07","<p>The following Iraqi nationals have been designated as core participants in the Al-Sweady Inquiry as they were either detained, or are related to those who died, during the engagements on 14 May 2004. All are represented by Public Interest Lawyers (PIL):<br><br>1. Hamzah Joudah Faraj ALMALJE<br>2. Mahdi Jasim Abdullah AL-BEHADILI <br>3. Ibrahim Gattan Hasan AL-ISMAEELI<br>4. Kadhim Abbas Lafta AL-BEHADILI <br>5. Abbas Abd Ali Abdulridha AL-HAMEEDAWI <br>6. Ahmed Jabbar Hammood AL-FURAIJI <br>7. Hussein Fadhil Abbas AL-BEHADILI <br>8. Atiyah Sayyid Abdulridha AL-BAIDHANI<br>9. Hussein Gubari Ali AL-LAMI <br>10. Kahz'al Jabratallah Khalad Mulla AL-HELFI <br>11. Hatar Moutashar Zeidan Shamekhy AL-LAMI <br>12. Khudhur Al-Swaiedi <br>13. Jasem Khalloufi Khreibet Al Alyawi AL-JAMINDARI <br>14. Ali Ati Raheemah AL-MOZANI<br>15. Rashak AL-AMSHANI<br>16. Sabrah Maryoosh HUSSEIN<br>17. Kamil Mowat Mohammed AL-MOZANI<br>18. Saad Radhi Khafeef AL-KEEMY<br>19. Yousef Ouda BADAY<br>20. Qassim Ghelan Neema Sahn AL-MAJIDI<br>21. Bareq Mohammed Hussein AL-KHALIFA <br>22. Ahmed Mshatat KAZEM<br>23. Karam Yaseen Laheet Sneshee AL-MOZANI <br>24. Zahra Resan MUHSIN<br>25. Abdelzahra Atti DAWOOD <br>26. Mahud Jihaijeh Dawood AL-MOZANI <br>27. Ali Jaseeb Ghazi AL-MUHAMMADAWI <br>28. Jabra Abdulah MOHSIN <br>29. Nasser Ali Husain AL-DOUGHAAN <br><br>The remaining Iraqi witnesses, most of whom are also represented by PIL, are considered by the Inquiry to be witnesses rather than core participants.<br><br>The Ministry of Defence (MoD) is also a core participant in the Inquiry as it is the Government Department that was responsible for the conduct of the British Servicemen who are the subject of allegations.<br><br>Although the Treasury Solicitor's Department is not a core participant, the Inquiry Chairman has accorded them equivalent status in recognition of the very large number (over 500) of current and former service personnel that they represent in this Inquiry. <br><br>A smaller number of military witnesses were either unrepresented or represented by Kennedy's and are considered witnesses, not core participants.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48789/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48789/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48789/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, who all the core participants in the Al-Sweady Inquiry  were; and what the name and firm was of each of those participants' legal representatives.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","196972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48790","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-05-06","<p>The Government has no plans to link the right to vote in General elections to residency rather than nationality.</p><p> </p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48790/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48790/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48790/answer",,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, if he will make an assessment of the feasibility of granting people the right to vote in General Elections based on residency rather than nationality; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","196936"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48791","Department for Education","false","2014-05-01","<p>The Department for Education hopes that any individual with relevant information about the serious allegations made in relation to a number of schools in Birmingham will come forward and share this with the Education Commissioner, Peter Clarke, and Ian Kershaw, the Chief Adviser for Birmingham City Council's investigation.</p><p>Amendments to The Employment Relations Act 1996, introduced by the Public Interest Disclosure Act (PIDA) 1998, mean that any confidentiality clauses in settlement agreements cannot have the effect of preventing a protected disclosure and any provision will be void to the extent it seeks to do so. The Department revised the model settlement agreements for new academies in January to make this absolutely clear. The PIDA Act 1998 also introduced provisions to protect workers from detrimental treatment or victimisation from their employer if, in the public interest, they blow the whistle on wrongdoing.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48791/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48791/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48791/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will take steps to remove any contractual gagging orders or similar measures applicable to staff in the West Midlands involved in the ongoing investigation into school governance in that area led by Ian Kershaw.","false","Biography information for Mr Khalid Mahmood","Birmingham, Perry Barr","Mr Khalid Mahmood","196860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48792","Department for Education","false","2014-05-01","<p>In February 2014 local authorities reported that around 103,000 two-year-olds were already accessing a funded early learning place. Local authorities are responsible for ensuring that every eligible child, whose parents wish them to take a place, is able to.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","196831","2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48792/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48792/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48792/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which local authorities currently do not have enough childcare places available to cater for the extension of the childcare offer to the 40 per cent most disadvantaged two-year-olds in September 2014; and what the shortfall of places is in each such authority.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","196830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48793","Department for Education","false","2014-05-01","<p>In February 2014 local authorities reported that around 103,000 two-year-olds were already accessing a funded early learning place. Local authorities are responsible for ensuring that every eligible child, whose parents wish them to take a place, is able to.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","196830","2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48793/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48793/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48793/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which local authorities currently do not have enough childcare places available to cater for the 20 per cent most disadvantaged two-year-olds; and what the shortfall is in each such authority.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","196831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48794","Department for Education","false","2014-05-06","<p>The Department for Education has published two reports on IES Breckland Free School:</p><p> </p><p>1. Impact assessment 2012, which is available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/251383/IES_Breckland-_Impact_Assessment_2012.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/251383/IES_Breckland-_Impact_Assessment_2012.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>2. Ofsted pre-registration advice note 2012, which is available at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/191634/ies_breckland.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/191634/ies_breckland.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In addition to the reports published by the Department, Ofsted published an inspection report on 13 March 2014, which is available at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/inspection-reports/find-inspection-report/provider/ELS/138250" target="_blank">http://www.ofsted.gov.uk/inspection-reports/find-inspection-report/provider/ELS/138250</a></p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48794/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48794/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48794/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what reports his Department has published on IES Breckland Free School.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","196832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48795","Department for Education","false","2014-05-06","<p>The Department for Education does not hold the information requested.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48795/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48795/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48795/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average cost was of a primary school meal in each local authority in (a) 2012 and (b) 2013.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","196878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48796","Department for Education","false","2014-05-06","<p>We have made it clear that, as schools implement the universal infant free school meals policy, they should ensure that pupils are routinely offered the option of a hot meal.</p><p> </p><p>We will monitor the take-up of school meals through the Schools Census for children in reception, year one and year two beginning in the autumn term of the 2014/15 academic year.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48796/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48796/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48796/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps his Department plans to take to monitor how many primary schools offer a hot meal option to all pupils in reception, year one and year two from September 2014.","false","Biography information for Andy Sawford","Corby","Andy Sawford","196829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48797","Department for Education","false","2014-05-01","<p>The facilitating subjects are identified by the Russell Group of universities as A level subjects that are required more often than others by universities. The list includes English literature along with mathematics, further mathematics, physics, biology, chemistry, geography, history and languages (classical and modern).</p><p>The Russell Group is an independent organisation; it recently reviewed the list of facilitating subjects and confirmed no change was needed. The Department for Education publishes a measure in the key stage 5 performance tables of the percentage of students achieving AAB grades at A level, including in at least two facilitating subjects.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","196816","2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48797/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48797/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48797/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will add economics, English literature and computing to the list of facilitating subjects for Key Stage 5 performance tables.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","196819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48798","Department for Education","false","2014-05-01","<p>The facilitating subjects are identified by the Russell Group of universities as A level subjects that are required more often than others by universities. The list includes English literature along with mathematics, further mathematics, physics, biology, chemistry, geography, history and languages (classical and modern).</p><p>The Russell Group is an independent organisation; it recently reviewed the list of facilitating subjects and confirmed no change was needed. The Department for Education publishes a measure in the key stage 5 performance tables of the percentage of students achieving AAB grades at A level, including in at least two facilitating subjects.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","196819","2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48798/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48798/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48798/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when he plans to review the list of facilitating subjects for Key Stage 5 performance tables.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","196816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48799","Department for Education","false","2014-05-01","<p>Any group or organisation can apply to the Department for Education to set up a free school. If approved, the proposers and any group members are involved in all aspects of project planning and design of the school. 175 free schools, 17 UTCs and 28 studio schools have been opened by groups including existing schools, academy sponsors, parents, teachers and community groups. A number of these have been in major new residential developments.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48799/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48799/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48799/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the oral Answer of 20 January 2014 from the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Planning, Official Report, column 7, on major developments (new schools), what scope there is for organisations other than local education authorities to be involved in the design, planning and sponsorship of new build primary and secondary schools in major new residential developments.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","196796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48800","Department for Education","false","2014-05-06","<p>The Secretary of State met the Minister for Education for Northern Ireland and the Minister of Education and Skills for Wales on May 13 2013, along with Ofqual's Chief Regulator Glenys Stacey, to discuss proposed reforms of GCSEs and A levels.</p><p> </p><p>In line with the concordats between the Department for Education and the Northern Ireland Government, we give the Ministers of the devolved Governments advance notice of our intentions wherever possible. Department for Education and Ofqual officials meet regularly with their counterparts in Wales and Northern Ireland to discuss matters of common interest and share information. This includes GCSE and A level reforms in their respective administrations.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48800/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48800/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48800/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what recent discussions he has held with education ministers in the devolved legislatures on proposals for English baccalaureate certificates and reforms of A-levels.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","196846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48801","Department for Education","false","2014-05-06","<p>The Department for Education does not hold a policy on who an appropriate person is to hold title deeds for schools funded by the UK taxpayer, as the law strictly controls the disposal of publicly-funded school land.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>When community schools convert to academies, the freehold is retained by the local authority and a lease is granted to the academy trust. In some circumstances, my Rt. hon Friend, the Secretary of State for Education, may allow publicly-funded school land to be transferred to a person concerned in the running of an academy. Where this occurs, the transfer will be to an academy trust, which will have satisfied the Secretary of State as to its ability to operate a state-funded school.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Mr Edward Timpson",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48801/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48801/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48801/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what his policy is on who is an appropriate person to hold title deeds for schools which are funded by the UK taxpayer; and whether those deeds can be sold or otherwise transferred.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","196804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48802","Department for Education","false","2014-05-06","<p>Funding for special educational needs (SEN) in England is not allocated as a separate amount per pupil. SEN funding is part of the overall Dedicated Schools Grant allocated to each local authority to fund their schools budget. It is for local authorities, in consultation with their schools forums, to determine the individual allocation to schools.</p><p> </p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48802/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48802/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48802/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much special educational needs funding per head his Department allocated to pupils in (a) Staffordshire, (b) Birmingham, (c) Wolverhampton and (d) the UK in (i) 2012-13, (ii) 2013-14 and (iii) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Gavin Williamson","South Staffordshire","Gavin Williamson","196894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48803","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-07","<p>The UK and Scottish Governments have both said that there can be no pre-negotiations on what the terms of Scottish independence might be before the referendum takes place on 18 September.</p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker","196843","2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48803/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48803/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48803/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether households in Scotland on the feed-in-tariff scheme will continue on that scheme for the duration of their contract in the event of a Yes vote in the referendum on Scottish independence.","false","Biography information for Mike Crockart","Edinburgh West","Mike Crockart","196842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48804","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-05-07","<p>The UK and Scottish Governments have both said that there can be no pre-negotiations on what the terms of Scottish independence might be before the referendum takes place on 18 September.</p>","Bexhill and Battle","Gregory Barker","196842","2014-05-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48804/answer","Biography information for Lord Barker of Battle","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48804/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48804/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what discussions he has had with the Scottish Government on the future of the feed-in-tariff scheme in Scotland in the event of a Yes vote in the referendum on Scottish independence.","false","Biography information for Mike Crockart","Edinburgh West","Mike Crockart","196843"
