"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48898","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-05-01","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The Social Fund Funeral Payment scheme continues to provide help towards a simple, respectful, low-cost funeral. In 2012/13, over 35,000 awards were made worth £42.7 million, with an average award of £1,225.</p><p> </p><p>Social Fund Budgeting Loans are also available to those on income related benefits to cover costs relating to funeral expenses.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, any arrears of benefit which were due to the deceased at date of death are disregarded. This means that such arrears are no longer deducted from the funeral payment award.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48898/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48898/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48898/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps he is taking to support people with the rising cost of funerals.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","196806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48928","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-01","<p>Phase one of the superfast roll-out programme is making good progress with all 44 projects in delivery.</p><p>Two thirds of projects (29 out of 44) have live superfast cabinets making superfast broadband available to thousands of homes and businesses across the country.</p><p>We are now investing the additional £250 million to take coverage of superfast broadband to 95% of UK premises</p><p> </p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48928/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48928/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48928/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he has taken to improve broadband coverage in rural areas.","false","Biography information for Alun Cairns","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","903806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49031","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-05-01","<p> </p><p> </p><p><em>The Government is committed to the protection and promotion of women's rights. Sharia law has no jurisdiction in England and Wales and the Government has no intention of changing this position. Everyone is equal before the law.</em></p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49031/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49031/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49031/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he is taking to ensure that women's rights are not undermined by the use of Sharia law.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","903799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49125","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-01","<p>The Health Surveys for England and Scotland show that the relationship between gambling related harm and deprivation is mixed. The proposals I announced yesterday will ensure that betting shop customers are subject to greater protections wherever they are based – whether that be areas of deprivation or otherwise.</p>","Maidstone and The Weald","Mrs Helen Grant",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49125/answer","Biography information for Mrs Helen Grant","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49125/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49125/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the effects of betting shops located in areas with high levels of deprivation on those areas.","false","Biography information for Meg Hillier","Hackney South and Shoreditch","Meg Hillier","903815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49375","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-01","<p>A new £10 million competitive fund opened on 21 March to market test innovative solutions to deliver superfast broadband services to the most difficult to reach remaining areas of the UK.</p><p>The pilot projects will explore how to reach these areas; and we'll use learning from the pilots to inform future government investment decisions</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49375/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49375/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49375/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to ensure that superfast broadband is available in remote areas of the UK.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bridgen","North West Leicestershire","Andrew Bridgen","903820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49376","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-01","<p>Parents tell us they want age ratings on music videos which are unsuitable for younger children.</p><p>We recently consulted on legislation to introduce BBFC age ratings for music DVDs unsuitable for children under 12. We expect to introduce the legislation to Parliament within the coming months and will bring the new age rating requirements into force as soon as possible.</p><p>I also welcome the commitment the music industry has made to pilot BBFC age ratings for online music videos.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49376/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49376/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49376/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when he plans to take steps to bring music video ratings into line with BBFC standards.","false","Biography information for Julie Hilling","Bolton West","Julie Hilling","903819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49377","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-05-01","<p>The value of all BBC services, including its local and regional services, should be considered as part of the review of the BBC's Charter. Government has yet to announce the timing, scope and process for Charter Review, so it would be premature to make any assessment at this point.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-05-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49377/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49377/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/49377/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-04-28",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the value of regional and local BBC services in discussions on the future financing of the BBC.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","903822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48403","Attorney General","false","2014-05-06","<p>These arrangements are kept under review.</p><p> </p>","North East Hertfordshire","Oliver Heald",,"2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48403/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48403/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48403/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2014-04-25",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, whether the Law Officers' Departments have any plans to end the employee trade union membership dues check-off system.","false","Biography information for Graeme Morrice","Livingston","Graeme Morrice","196759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48404","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-06","<p>The announced changes to Disabled Students' Allowances (DSAs) will be subject to a full equality analysis to determine the impact of these changes on students with protected characteristics. The equality analysis will be given full consideration before regulations are laid before the House.</p><p> </p><p>These changes will apply to all full-time, full-time distance learning, part-time and postgraduate students in higher education applying for DSA for the first time from the 2015/16 academic year. DSAs are not available to further education students, as the Government provides Learning Support funding to further education colleges and providers to help meet the additional needs of learners with learning difficulties and/or disabilities.</p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts","196514","2014-05-06T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48404/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48404/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48404/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-25",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether he has carried out an equalities impact assessment of the changes to disabled students' allowances which were announced on 7 April 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","196612"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48405","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-05-08","<p>Each year the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) and the Devolved Administrations set Student Loans Company (SLC) stretching performance measures which are confirmed in an Annual Performance and Resource Agreement (APRA) letter. BIS closely monitors SLC's performance against these measures throughout the year. Monitoring arrangements include formal quarterly reviews of SLC's performance which are conducted by Ministers and senior officials.</p><p> </p><p>Each year the SLC publishes externally audited information on its performance in its Annual Report and Accounts. The APRA letter and SLC's Annual Report and Accounts are available on SLC's website: <a href="http://www.slc.co.uk/" target="_blank">http://www.slc.co.uk/</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts",,"2014-05-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48405/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48405/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/48405/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-04-25",,"1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what audit he has made of the performance of the Student Loans Company.","false","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","196697"
